{"type":"message","id":"59ee5e3e","parentId":"6643c9b6","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:51:11.534Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_zL6jQJrIxQvk2La53hT9OuqY","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: send-email\ndescription: Send emails via SMTP. Configure in ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json under skills.entries.send-email.env.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"emoji\":\"📧\",\"requires\":{\"anyBins\":[\"python3\"]}}}\n---\n\n# Send Email\n\nSend emails via the Python script. SMTP settings are **injected by OpenClaw at runtime** when the script runs (from `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` → `skills.entries.send-email.env`). **Do not read** any config file (e.g. `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` or `workspace/openclaw.json`) — that would expose credentials in tool output. Just run the script; env is injected automatically. Do not use ~/.msmtprc.\n\n## Configuration\n\nConfigure in **`~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`**:\n\n```json\n\"skills\": {\n  \"entries\": {\n    \"send-email\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"env\": {\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER\": \"smtp.163.com\",\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_PORT\": \"465\",\n        \"EMAIL_SENDER\": \"your-email@163.com\",\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD\": \"YOUR_AUTH_CODE\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER | SMTP server, e.g. smtp.163.com, smtp.gmail.com |\n| EMAIL_SMTP_PORT | Port, 465 (SSL) or 587 (TLS) |\n| EMAIL_SENDER | Sender email address |\n| EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD | Authorization code / app password (163/QQ: auth code; Gmail: App Password) |\n\n## Agent instructions\n\n1. **Credentials**: Never read config files. OpenClaw injects `skills.entries.send-email.env` when the script runs — do not use the read tool on `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` or `workspace/openclaw.json` (exposes secrets). If the skill is enabled, assume env is configured; do not ask the user for passwords. Do not use ~/.msmtprc.\n2. **Send mail**: Run the script under **workspace** (do not use the path under node_modules):\n   ```bash\n   python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient\" \"Subject\" \"Body\"\n   ```\n3. **Attachment**: `python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient\" \"Subject\" \"Body\" \"/path/to/file.pdf\"`\n\n## Usage examples\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py 'recipient@example.com' 'Subject' 'Body text'\npython3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py 'recipient@example.com' 'Subject' 'Body' '/path/to/file.pdf'\n```\n\n## SMTP reference\n\n- 163: `smtp.163.com:465`, requires authorization code (not login password)\n- Gmail: `smtp.gmail.com:587`, requires App Password\n- QQ: `smtp.qq.com:465`, requires authorization code\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n- Authentication failed: Check that `EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD` is the authorization code or App Password.\n- Connection failed: Check `EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER` and `EMAIL_SMTP_PORT`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775814671508}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0e85df4","parentId":"59ee5e3e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:51:18.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `send-email` skill is configured to send emails via a Python script using SMTP. Here’s a summary of how it works and what you need:\n\n### Configuration Details\nTo enable the skill, SMTP settings must be properly configured in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:\n\n```json\n\"skills\": {\n  \"entries\": {\n    \"send-email\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"env\": {\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER\": \"smtp.163.com\",\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_PORT\": \"465\",\n        \"EMAIL_SENDER\": \"your-email@163.com\",\n        \"EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD\": \"YOUR_AUTH_CODE\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nEach field represents:\n- **EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER**: The SMTP server address (e.g., `smtp.gmail.com`, `smtp.163.com`).\n- **EMAIL_SMTP_PORT**: Port to use (e.g., 465 for SSL, 587 for TLS).\n- **EMAIL_SENDER**: The sender’s email address.\n- **EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD**: The authorization code or app password (NOT the regular email account password).\n\n### How It Works\n1. **Environment Variables**: OpenClaw injects the email settings automatically; you don’t need to read them directly.\n2. **Send Mail Command**: The script is executed in the workspace:\n   ```bash\n   python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient\" \"Subject\" \"Body\"\n   ```\n3. **Attachments**: You can add an attachment:\n   ```bash\n   python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient\" \"Subject\" \"Body\" \"/path/to/file.pdf\"\n   ```\n\n### Example Troubleshooting\n- **Authentication Issues**: Verify that the provided password matches the app password or SMTP authorization code.\n- **Connection Problems**: Ensure the correct server and port are specified.\n\nIf you need assistance setting up the SMTP configuration, let me know! Otherwise, ensure the configuration is ready, and I can reattempt sending the email."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"github-copilot","model":"gpt-4o","usage":{"input":761,"output":438,"cacheRead":17792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18991,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775814671535,"responseId":"chatcmpl-DT2o5ccLuiJhXfTk56khA86OwFLC5"}}
